The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Dutts high-tech agenda 
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta, June 26: Advancement of technology and fitness training will be high on the agenda of the sports policy, Union minister of sports Sunil Dutt said on Saturday. Dutt, who was in the city to attend the 32nd national inter-school regatta meet at Lake Club, said: Fitness training centres will be set up in every state and the focus will be on nurturing talent from the rural areas. Only with technological finesse coupled with fitness can we compete on the international arena, said the minister. He added: sports will be made compulsory in schools. The minister also announced that 12 medal winners (three each from four categories) at the regatta event would receive free education for the next two years sponsored by the sports ministry.  Copyright 
